{"ev": "seen", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "story": {"id": "st-a94899b19003", "date": "2026-07-22", "stream": "news", "headline": "US concludes 11th round of strikes on Iran as Houthis blockade Bab al-Mandeb; Hegseth seeks $87.6bn more", "summary": "The US-Israel war on Iran widened as Yemen's Houthis closed the Bab al-Mandeb strait and Hegseth told senators the war has cost the US $37.5bn.", "url": "https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/7/22/iran-gulf-hit-as-hormuz-bab-al-mandeb-close-whats-the-latest", "source_domain": "aljazeera.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["geopolitics", "security"], "importance": 3, "display_body": "The US-Israel war on Iran widened into the Red Sea on Tuesday 21 July as Yemen's Houthis declared a naval blockade of Saudi Arabia, closing the Bab al-Mandeb strait. Two oil tankers carrying Saudi crude toward Asia turned back after the announcement, compounding disruption already hitting the Strait of Hormuz - the two chokepoints together carry a large share of seaborne oil. The US said it had concluded its 11th round of strikes on Iran and Tehran retaliated; Washington is reportedly weighing an attack on Iran's Pickaxe Mountain, believed to be an underground uranium-enrichment site. Testifying to senators on Wednesday 22 July, Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth put the war's cost to the US at $37.5bn so far and requested $87.6bn more, while Secretary of State Marco Rubio said the US remains open to negotiations but that Iran is not serious.", "why": "A second closed chokepoint turns a regional war into a direct shock to global energy shipping, and the funding request signals Washington is bracing for a long campaign, not a quick strike.", "thread_id": "2026-07-22-news-us-concludes-11th-round-of-strikes-on-iran-as-ho", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-22", "event_date": "2026-07-22", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Iran", "United States", "Houthis", "Bab al-Mandeb", "Strait of Hormuz"], "status": "settled", "first_seen": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "updated": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "legacy_ids": ["2026-07-22-news-us-concludes-11th-round-of-strikes-on-iran-as-ho"], "editions": ["2026-07-22-news"], "origin": "writer:news", "streams": ["news"]}}
{"ev": "publish", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "id": "st-a94899b19003", "edition": "2026-07-22-news", "fields": {"display_body": "The US-Israel war on Iran widened into the Red Sea on Tuesday 21 July as Yemen's Houthis declared a naval blockade of Saudi Arabia, closing the Bab al-Mandeb strait. Two oil tankers carrying Saudi crude toward Asia turned back after the announcement, compounding disruption already hitting the Strait of Hormuz - the two chokepoints together carry a large share of seaborne oil. The US said it had concluded its 11th round of strikes on Iran and Tehran retaliated; Washington is reportedly weighing an attack on Iran's Pickaxe Mountain, believed to be an underground uranium-enrichment site. Testifying to senators on Wednesday 22 July, Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth put the war's cost to the US at $37.5bn so far and requested $87.6bn more, while Secretary of State Marco Rubio said the US remains open to negotiations but that Iran is not serious.", "why": "A second closed chokepoint turns a regional war into a direct shock to global energy shipping, and the funding request signals Washington is bracing for a long campaign, not a quick strike.", "importance": 3, "status": "settled"}}
{"ev": "seen", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "story": {"id": "st-de759cb0e829", "date": "2026-07-22", "stream": "news", "headline": "Zelensky dismisses armed-forces chief Syrsky amid protests, names Drapaty", "summary": "Ukraine's president fired commander-in-chief Oleksandr Syrsky on Tuesday and replaced him with Mykhailo Drapaty after protests.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/en-direct-guerre-en-ukraine-volodymyr-zelensky-limoge-le-commandant-en-chef-de-son-armee", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["geopolitics", "politics"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "President Volodymyr Zelensky dismissed the commander-in-chief of Ukraine's armed forces, Oleksandr Syrsky, on Tuesday 21 July, and named the popular joint-forces commander Mykhailo Drapaty to replace him. The move follows the 15 July sacking of young defence minister Mykhailo Fedorov - the architect of Ukraine's drone force - which set off mass protests in Kyiv; demonstrators had accused the military leadership of wasting lives. Le Temps frames the shake-up as Zelensky sidelining modernisers in favour of the old guard.", "why": "Replacing both the defence minister and the top general inside a week, under public pressure, points to a real doctrinal fight over how Ukraine fights the war - and rare open dissent at home.", "thread_id": "2026-07-22-news-zelensky-dismisses-armed-forces-chief-syrsky-ami", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-22", "event_date": "2026-07-21", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Ukraine", "Volodymyr Zelensky", "Oleksandr Syrsky", "Mykhailo Drapaty"], "status": "settled", "first_seen": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "updated": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "legacy_ids": ["2026-07-22-news-zelensky-dismisses-armed-forces-chief-syrsky-ami"], "editions": ["2026-07-22-news"], "origin": "writer:news", "streams": ["news"]}}
{"ev": "publish", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "id": "st-de759cb0e829", "edition": "2026-07-22-news", "fields": {"display_body": "President Volodymyr Zelensky dismissed the commander-in-chief of Ukraine's armed forces, Oleksandr Syrsky, on Tuesday 21 July, and named the popular joint-forces commander Mykhailo Drapaty to replace him. The move follows the 15 July sacking of young defence minister Mykhailo Fedorov - the architect of Ukraine's drone force - which set off mass protests in Kyiv; demonstrators had accused the military leadership of wasting lives. Le Temps frames the shake-up as Zelensky sidelining modernisers in favour of the old guard.", "why": "Replacing both the defence minister and the top general inside a week, under public pressure, points to a real doctrinal fight over how Ukraine fights the war - and rare open dissent at home.", "importance": 2, "status": "settled"}}
{"ev": "seen", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "story": {"id": "st-b0401f616d4b", "date": "2026-07-22", "stream": "news", "headline": "US to sign deal giving Saudi Arabia a civil uranium-enrichment program", "summary": "The Trump administration is expected to announce a deal for US firms to build a uranium enrichment complex in Saudi Arabia.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/les-etats-unis-s-entendent-avec-l-arabie-saoudite-pour-la-doter-d-un-programme-nucleaire-civil", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["single-source"], "topics": ["geopolitics"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "The Trump administration is expected to announce Wednesday 22 July a deal under which US firms would build a uranium-enrichment complex in Saudi Arabia, giving the kingdom a civil nuclear programme. Officials stress the programme is meant for civilian use; critics warn that endorsing enrichment on Saudi soil - as the US is actively bombing Iran to stop its own enrichment - could accelerate a regional arms race.", "why": "Enrichment is the dual-use step that separates a power reactor from a bomb, so a US-blessed Saudi enrichment plant reshapes the Gulf's proliferation math at the worst possible moment.", "thread_id": "2026-07-22-news-us-to-sign-deal-giving-saudi-arabia-a-civil-uran", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-22", "event_date": "2026-07-22", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["United States", "Saudi Arabia", "Donald Trump"], "status": "settled", "first_seen": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "updated": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "legacy_ids": ["2026-07-22-news-us-to-sign-deal-giving-saudi-arabia-a-civil-uran"], "editions": ["2026-07-22-news"], "origin": "writer:news", "streams": ["news"]}}
{"ev": "publish", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "id": "st-b0401f616d4b", "edition": "2026-07-22-news", "fields": {"display_body": "The Trump administration is expected to announce Wednesday 22 July a deal under which US firms would build a uranium-enrichment complex in Saudi Arabia, giving the kingdom a civil nuclear programme. Officials stress the programme is meant for civilian use; critics warn that endorsing enrichment on Saudi soil - as the US is actively bombing Iran to stop its own enrichment - could accelerate a regional arms race.", "why": "Enrichment is the dual-use step that separates a power reactor from a bomb, so a US-blessed Saudi enrichment plant reshapes the Gulf's proliferation math at the worst possible moment.", "importance": 2, "status": "settled"}}
{"ev": "seen", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "story": {"id": "st-6c58b0144575", "date": "2026-07-22", "stream": "news", "headline": "France adopts EU-first ban on social media for under-15s", "summary": "The French Parliament definitively adopted a Macron-backed law barring under-15s from social media, effective September.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/la-france-s-apprete-a-interdire-les-reseaux-sociaux-aux-moins-de-15-ans-une-premiere-en-europe", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["politics", "tech"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "The French Parliament definitively adopted on Tuesday 21 July a law barring under-15s from social media - a European first - with the ban set to take effect in September. The Macron-backed text requires platforms to verify users' ages but sets no penalty for families, a gap that drew criticism as unworkable. This finalises the bill the two chambers were only scheduled to vote on a day earlier.", "why": "It is the first hard national age floor for social media in the EU, and a live test of whether platform-side age verification can be enforced at all - with implications for how neighbouring states, including Switzerland, regulate minors online.", "thread_id": "2026-07-22-news-france-adopts-eu-first-ban-on-social-media-for-u", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-22", "event_date": "2026-07-21", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["France", "Emmanuel Macron"], "status": "settled", "first_seen": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "updated": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "legacy_ids": ["2026-07-22-news-france-adopts-eu-first-ban-on-social-media-for-u"], "editions": ["2026-07-22-news"], "origin": "writer:news", "streams": ["news"]}}
{"ev": "publish", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "id": "st-6c58b0144575", "edition": "2026-07-22-news", "fields": {"display_body": "The French Parliament definitively adopted on Tuesday 21 July a law barring under-15s from social media - a European first - with the ban set to take effect in September. The Macron-backed text requires platforms to verify users' ages but sets no penalty for families, a gap that drew criticism as unworkable. This finalises the bill the two chambers were only scheduled to vote on a day earlier.", "why": "It is the first hard national age floor for social media in the EU, and a live test of whether platform-side age verification can be enforced at all - with implications for how neighbouring states, including Switzerland, regulate minors online.", "importance": 2, "status": "settled"}}
{"ev": "seen", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "story": {"id": "st-85465ae3bab5", "date": "2026-07-22", "stream": "news", "headline": "Trump's 100% generic-drug tariff puts Swiss maker Sandoz on front line", "summary": "Trump announced 100% tariffs on imported generic drugs from 2028, exposing Sandoz whose production is largely in Europe.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/les-menaces-de-donald-trump-sur-les-generiques-placent-sandoz-en-premiere-ligne", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["single-source"], "topics": ["economy", "switzerland"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "Donald Trump's threatened 100% tariff on imported generic drugs, announced Tuesday 21 July and slated to start in 2028, lands squarely on Swiss-based Sandoz. The world's leading generics maker manufactures largely in Europe, so a US import levy - which Washington says is meant to relocate production stateside and which could rise to 200% in 2029 - would hit its US business hard.", "why": "Generics are a thin-margin, high-volume business, and a tariff of this size is less a price signal than a demand to rebuild supply chains, a direct threat to a major Swiss pharma employer.", "thread_id": "2026-07-22-news-trump-s-100-generic-drug-tariff-puts-swiss-maker", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-22", "event_date": "2026-07-21", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Sandoz", "Donald Trump", "United States"], "status": "settled", "first_seen": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "updated": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "legacy_ids": ["2026-07-22-news-trump-s-100-generic-drug-tariff-puts-swiss-maker"], "editions": ["2026-07-22-news"], "origin": "writer:news", "streams": ["news"]}}
{"ev": "publish", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "id": "st-85465ae3bab5", "edition": "2026-07-22-news", "fields": {"display_body": "Donald Trump's threatened 100% tariff on imported generic drugs, announced Tuesday 21 July and slated to start in 2028, lands squarely on Swiss-based Sandoz. The world's leading generics maker manufactures largely in Europe, so a US import levy - which Washington says is meant to relocate production stateside and which could rise to 200% in 2029 - would hit its US business hard.", "why": "Generics are a thin-margin, high-volume business, and a tariff of this size is less a price signal than a demand to rebuild supply chains, a direct threat to a major Swiss pharma employer.", "importance": 2, "status": "settled"}}
{"ev": "seen", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "story": {"id": "st-6d9a7317fa5a", "date": "2026-07-22", "stream": "news", "headline": "Geneva court suspends canton's pool ban on long swimwear and burkini", "summary": "Geneva justice granted suspensive effect to an appeal against the late-May law banning long clothing in public pools.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/a-geneve-la-loi-interdisant-le-burkini-est-suspendue", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["switzerland", "politics"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "Geneva's justice system has suspended the canton's contested law banning long swimwear - including the burkini - in public pools, granting suspensive effect to an appeal. The law took force at the end of May but is now blocked pending the case; it is also being challenged by five communes, among them the city of Geneva itself.", "why": "The suspension is the first serious legal setback for one of Switzerland's most divisive recent cantonal measures, and pits the canton against its own largest city.", "thread_id": "2026-07-22-news-geneva-court-suspends-canton-s-pool-ban-on-long", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-22", "event_date": "2026-07-22", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Geneva"], "status": "settled", "first_seen": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "updated": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "legacy_ids": ["2026-07-22-news-geneva-court-suspends-canton-s-pool-ban-on-long"], "editions": ["2026-07-22-news"], "origin": "writer:news", "streams": ["news"]}}
{"ev": "publish", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "id": "st-6d9a7317fa5a", "edition": "2026-07-22-news", "fields": {"display_body": "Geneva's justice system has suspended the canton's contested law banning long swimwear - including the burkini - in public pools, granting suspensive effect to an appeal. The law took force at the end of May but is now blocked pending the case; it is also being challenged by five communes, among them the city of Geneva itself.", "why": "The suspension is the first serious legal setback for one of Switzerland's most divisive recent cantonal measures, and pits the canton against its own largest city.", "importance": 2, "status": "settled"}}
{"ev": "seen", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "story": {"id": "st-d223d712a040", "date": "2026-07-22", "stream": "news", "headline": "Skyguide facing structural deficit; transport politicians seek new revenue", "summary": "Swiss air-navigation firm Skyguide faces a CHF40m annual structural deficit from 2030; politicians propose charging foreign users or passengers.", "url": "https://www.srf.ch/news/schweiz/deutschland-soll-zahlen-verkehrspolitiker-verlangen-neue-einnahmequellen-fuer-skyguide", "source_domain": "srf.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["switzerland", "economy"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "Swiss air-navigation provider Skyguide faces a structural deficit of about CHF 40 million a year from 2030, and transport politicians are pushing for new revenue sources. Skyguide lives mainly on fees airlines pay for landings and overflights, with the Confederation - its main shareholder - already contributing over CHF 120 million for special tasks such as military air control and services in cross-border airspace; that no longer covers costs. Ideas floated include recovering fees from foreign users of Swiss-controlled airspace or charging passengers directly, alongside a federal cost-cutting programme.", "why": "The funding gap forces a choice between higher travel costs and cuts at an operator that has had high-profile outages, touching both flight safety and ticket prices.", "thread_id": "2026-07-22-news-skyguide-facing-structural-deficit-transport-pol", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-22", "event_date": "2026-07-22", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Skyguide", "Switzerland"], "status": "settled", "first_seen": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "updated": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "legacy_ids": ["2026-07-22-news-skyguide-facing-structural-deficit-transport-pol"], "editions": ["2026-07-22-news"], "origin": "writer:news", "streams": ["news"]}}
{"ev": "publish", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "id": "st-d223d712a040", "edition": "2026-07-22-news", "fields": {"display_body": "Swiss air-navigation provider Skyguide faces a structural deficit of about CHF 40 million a year from 2030, and transport politicians are pushing for new revenue sources. Skyguide lives mainly on fees airlines pay for landings and overflights, with the Confederation - its main shareholder - already contributing over CHF 120 million for special tasks such as military air control and services in cross-border airspace; that no longer covers costs. Ideas floated include recovering fees from foreign users of Swiss-controlled airspace or charging passengers directly, alongside a federal cost-cutting programme.", "why": "The funding gap forces a choice between higher travel costs and cuts at an operator that has had high-profile outages, touching both flight safety and ticket prices.", "importance": 1, "status": "settled"}}
{"ev": "seen", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "story": {"id": "st-1c5a85c790ad", "date": "2026-07-22", "stream": "news", "headline": "Swiss drownings rise; at least 15 deaths in a month", "summary": "The Swiss Lifesaving Society says bathing deaths are up year-on-year, with at least 15 drownings in a month.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/le-nombre-de-noyades-a-augmente-cette-annee-sur-les-plans-d-eau-suisses", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["switzerland"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "At least 15 people have drowned in Switzerland in the past month, and the Swiss Lifesaving Society reports bathing deaths running above last year's pace. Two of the recent deaths were in the river Aare; men account for a markedly higher share of cases than women, per SRF. The running toll is still below the exceptional 2022 and 2023 summers.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-22-news-swiss-drownings-rise-at-least-15-deaths-in-a-mon", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-22", "event_date": "2026-07-22", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Switzerland", "Aare"], "status": "settled", "first_seen": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "updated": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "legacy_ids": ["2026-07-22-news-swiss-drownings-rise-at-least-15-deaths-in-a-mon"], "editions": ["2026-07-22-news"], "origin": "writer:news", "streams": ["news"]}}
{"ev": "publish", "ts": "2026-07-22T10:13:07Z", "actor": "news", "id": "st-1c5a85c790ad", "edition": "2026-07-22-news", "fields": {"display_body": "At least 15 people have drowned in Switzerland in the past month, and the Swiss Lifesaving Society reports bathing deaths running above last year's pace. Two of the recent deaths were in the river Aare; men account for a markedly higher share of cases than women, per SRF. The running toll is still below the exceptional 2022 and 2023 summers.", "why": "", "importance": 1, "status": "settled"}}
